    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cheerleading? Bah!</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Miryam Antunez de Mayolo letter disputes September 3 Week in Review article on cheerleaders</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Where a Teenager Gives Orders'' (Week in Review, Sept. 3):</p>
        <p>It does not matter that cheerleading today demands choreographic or physical skill; the bottom line is that it remains a sideline activity engaged in by scantily clad young women with the purpose of applauding mostly male achievement and triumph.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Where a Teenager Gives Orders'' (Week in Review, Sept. 3):</p>
        <p>It does not matter that cheerleading today demands choreographic or physical skill; the bottom line is that it remains a sideline activity engaged in by scantily clad young women with the purpose of applauding mostly male achievement and triumph.</p>
        <p>I have two young daughters whom I'd rather see making their own triumphs instead of celebrating those of their male schoolmates.</p>
        <p>MIRYAM ANTUNEZ DE MAYOLO  Waterloo, Iowa, Sept. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
